Tested on:
RedHat 5, RedHat 6 , Debian Lenny ( required to run snmp as root )

Prerequisites:

net-snmp server
net-snmp-perl modules

in the order the included sample to work you also need /usr/sbin/ntpdate utility.

Installation:

1. create a directory under snmp configuration. as an instance:
   mkdir /etc/snmp/subagent

2. copy all files to the directory

3. add line to snmpd.conf:
perl do "/etc/snmp/subagent/snmpd-poller-agent";

4. optional. read and amend snmpd-poller.conf  
   you may need to amend time server name ( see line 40 )

5. restart snmpd server

Verification:

snmpwalk -v1 -c public localhost -On .1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1.1.1 = STRING: "-0.000784"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1.2.1 = STRING: "/usr/sbin/ntpdate -t 10 -q4 ntp|"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1.2.2 = STRING: "0.341"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1.2.3 = STRING: "0"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1000.1.1 = STRING: "1308844535.0951"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1000.2.1 = STRING: "PStat"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1000.2.2 = STRING: "0.360"
.1.3.6.1.4.1.777.107.1000.2.3 = STRING: "0"

Troubleshuting:
Check system log for errors
Read the source :)
